We wish you a full of laughter and health week!
Few tips from our family to stay healthy this season ✨

🥗 cook, cook, cook!
Plant based and whole foods
Eat grounding and in season foods - root vegetables.
Less sugar!
Warm liquids (lemon water, soups..)
Snack on mini bell peppers- they are vit C bombs 💣 
Keep on moving 🤾‍♀️

Suppliment:
🌿 Vit C (our bodies does not make it) the best ones for little ones @maryruthorganics 
🌿Zinc (love by @maryruthorganics one)
Gentle and delicious tasting 
🌿Vit D for extra ☀️
🍂Avoid sugary multivitamins!

Stay well!💪🏼🙌🏼😘
Love and light to you!

#theskaringalifestyle #healthtips #healthytoddler #livingourbestlife #healthtips

"The Dreamer"
By Agne Skaringa
Oil and Gold Leaf on canvas
48" x 48"
2023

The paragraph can be improved as follows:

The painting depicts a woman floating inside a bubble, symbolizing her life being shaped by her vivid imagination. The woman in the bubble conveys the idea that we have the power to perceive the world in its most positive light. The fragile nature of idealism is represented by the bubble, which could burst at any moment, causing her to fall. The circular composition and the damp atmosphere evoke a sense of returning to our origins, reminiscent of the safety and comfort of a mother's womb. The painting is characterized by its vibrant colors, evoking positive emotions within viewers. Some bubbles are adorned with delicate words, such as "spirit," "dream," and "vision," mirroring their fragility, just like bubbles. Multiple layers of high-gloss varnish cover the bubbles, creating a radiant 3D effect.

"Let it go"
by Agne Skaringa @artistagne 
Oil on canvas
60 x 60 inches
2010

  This painting is a symbol to an inner liberation.
At first glance the observer,as a dark crow,
feels obscured and concerned.
 The woman sitting on the bar is full of inner emotions, that are possessed to the observer.
Once the observer is synchronized with the woman ,the energy begins to flow up through the body. It is released through the cigarette, through hair allowing the observer to escape to an inner liberation.

#fineart #oiloncanvas #oilpaintingwoman #selfportrait #losangelesfineartist #innerliberation #innerliberationhealing
